					<h3>
    					An Innovation Cafe Workshop: DeepDive into improving collaboration between agencies
    				</h3>
					<p>
				  Deloitte Consulting will facilitate this interactive workshop and provide an introduction to a framework for considering three different system factors that determine the extent of information sharing between agencies:</p>
					<ul>
					  <li> 
					    The rules governing the sharing of information or standard operating procedures that impact information flow,					</li>
					  <li>The level of priority within each agency afforded to the need to share data within the agency and with criminal justice system partners, and
				      </li>
					  <li>
					    Capabilities - the skills and resources and systems within agencies that support information sharing					  </li>
				  </ul>
					<p>Participants will leave this session with an understanding of drivers and insight on how they could improve upon each to better support greater information sharing. Each table will then discuss one of those drivers for a third of the remaining time and brainstorm ideas for how they could improve them so that they support greater information sharing.				    </p>
